subSection.paragraph:
Remarks:
This has been previously recorded in Mt. Makiling which confirms its distribution in the Southern Luzon area. Interestingly, the aedeagus observed in this study resembles the aedeagus specimen from Busuanga Island (
Sivec 1984
) in which the island was once connected to mainland Asia while Luzon is oceanic in origin (
Hall 2002
).

